## 2. Ideal Gas Law & Isentropic Processes

```elixir
p1_input = Kino.Input.number("Initial pressure P₁ (bar)", default: 1.0)
t1_input = Kino.Input.number("Initial temperature T₁ (°C)", default: 20.0)
r_input  = Kino.Input.number("Compression ratio P₂/P₁", default: 10.0)
Kino.Layout.grid([p1_input, t1_input, r_input], columns: 3)
```

```elixir
p1 = Kino.Input.read(p1_input) * 1e5  # to Pa
t1 = Kino.Input.read(t1_input) + 273.15
r  = Kino.Input.read(r_input)
p2 = p1 * r

iso = EnergyX.Thermal.Thermodynamics.isentropic_process(%{t1_k: t1, p1: p1, p2: p2})

v1 = EnergyX.Thermal.Thermodynamics.ideal_gas(:v, %{p: p1, n: 1.0, t_k: t1})
v2 = EnergyX.Thermal.Thermodynamics.ideal_gas(:v, %{p: p2, n: 1.0, t_k: iso.t2_k})

IO.puts("""
Isentropic compression (γ = 1.4):
  State 1: P₁ = #{Float.round(p1/1e5, 2)} bar | T₁ = #{Float.round(t1-273.15, 1)}°C | V₁ = #{Float.round(v1.v_m3*1000, 3)} L/mol
  State 2: P₂ = #{Float.round(p2/1e5, 2)} bar | T₂ = #{Float.round(iso.t2_c, 1)}°C | V₂ = #{Float.round(v2.v_m3*1000, 3)} L/mol
  Temperature rise: #{Float.round(iso.t2_k - t1, 1)} K
""")
```

