## 5. Fluid Mechanics — Pipe Flow

```elixir
flow_v     = Kino.Input.number("Flow velocity (m/s)", default: 2.5)
diameter   = Kino.Input.number("Pipe diameter (mm)",  default: 100.0)
pipe_len   = Kino.Input.number("Pipe length (m)",     default: 100.0)
Kino.Layout.grid([flow_v, diameter, pipe_len], columns: 3)
```

```elixir
v = Kino.Input.read(flow_v)
d = Kino.Input.read(diameter) / 1000.0
l = Kino.Input.read(pipe_len)

re_res = EnergyX.Thermal.FluidMechanics.reynolds(%{rho: 1000.0, velocity: v, diameter: d, viscosity_dyn: 1.0e-3})
ff_res = EnergyX.Thermal.FluidMechanics.friction_factor(%{re: re_res.reynolds, relative_roughness: 4.5e-5 / d})
dp_res = EnergyX.Thermal.FluidMechanics.pressure_drop(%{f: ff_res.friction_factor, length_m: l,
           diameter_m: d, rho: 1000.0, velocity: v})

pump   = EnergyX.Thermal.FluidMechanics.pump_power(%{rho: 1000.0,
           flow_m3_s: v * :math.pi * d * d / 4.0,
           head_m: dp_res.pressure_drop_pa / (1000.0 * 9.81),
           eta_pump: 0.78})

IO.puts("""
Pipe Flow Analysis (water, ε/D = #{Float.round(4.5e-5/d, 6)})
────────────────────────────────────────────
Reynolds number:  #{trunc(re_res.reynolds)} → #{re_res.regime}
Friction factor f: #{Float.round(ff_res.friction_factor, 6)} (Darcy-Weisbach)
Pressure drop:    #{Float.round(dp_res.pressure_drop_pa/1000, 3)} kPa over #{l} m
Pump power:       #{Float.round(pump.shaft_power_kw, 3)} kW (η=78%)
""")
```

